election_record.label: New Hampshire 1812 Governor

candidate.name: Johnson
candidate.note: Listed in Original Election Returns as Captain Johnson.

candidate.name: Whipple
candidate.note: Listed in Original Election Returns as Colonel Whipple.

overview.note: New Hampshire law required a majority for election. The election passed to the State Legislature. As the Republicans controlled the Legislature, William Plumer was elected.

sub_unit.name: Sharon
sub_unit.note: John T. Gilman received 13 votes as John T. Gilm.
